A 34-year-old man from Amaoti outside Durban who stabbed and cut open his girlfriend’s stomach was shot dead by police officers on Saturday. Ipid spokesperson, Grace Langa said the police officers from Inanda police station found the man cutting his girlfriend’s stomach and taking out body parts after he had stabbed her to death. “They found him taking out intestines and the action looked like someone who was conducting a postmortem,” said Langa. She said police tried to stop the man but he instead attacked the officers. He was shot and died at the scene. Langa said the woman has not been identified and her family is unknown. She was renting a room at number C37 Zambia Amaoti. The man had visited her. Three empty 9mm cartridges and the knife used to stab the woman were recovered at the scene.